obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (32360)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00041_197814_1517807325128&sectionId=32360&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00041_197814_1517807325128
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Interest Act, 1978.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India except the State of Jammu and Kashmir*.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `*. Vide Notification No. S.O. 3912 (E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu`
  line `and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
  line
  line `1. 19th August, 1981, vide notification No. S.O. 657(E), dated 19th August, 1981, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (32361)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00041_197814_1517807325128&sectionId=32361&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00041_197814_1517807325128
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "court" includes a tribunal and an arbitrator;`
  line
  line `(b) "current rate of interest" means the highest of the maximum rates at which interest may be`
  line `paid on different classes of deposits (other than those maintained in savings account or those`
  line `maintained by charitable or religious institutions) by different classes of scheduled banks in`
  line `accordance with the directions given or issued to banking companies generally by the Reserve Bank`
  line `of India under the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949).`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this clause, "scheduled bank" means a bank, not being a co-operative bank,`
  line `transacting any business authorised by the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949);`
  line
  line `(c) "debt" means by liability for an ascertained sum of money and includes a debt payable in`
  line `kind, but does not include a judgment debt;`
  line
  line `(d) "personal injuries" includes any disease and any impairment of a person's physical or mental`
  line condition;
  line
  line `(e) all other words and expressions used herein but not defined and defined in the Reserve Bank`
  line `of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934), shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (32362)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Power of court to allow interest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00041_197814_1517807325128&sectionId=32362&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00041_197814_1517807325128
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) In any proceedings for the recovery of any debt or`
  line `damages or in any proceedings in which a claim for interest in respect of any debt or damages already`
  line `paid is made, the court may, if it thinks fit, allow interest to the person entitled to the debt or damages or`
  line `to the person making such claim, as the case may be, at a rate not exceeding the current rate of interest,`
  line `for the whole or part of the following period, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) if the proceedings relate to a debt payable by virtue of a written instrument at a certain time,`
  line `then, from the date when the debt is payable to the date of institution of the proceedings;`
  line
  line `(b) if the proceedings do not relate to any such debt, then, from the date mentioned in this regard`
  line `in a written notice given by the person entitled or the person making the claim to the person liable that`
  line `interest will be claimed, to the date of institution of the proceedings:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the amount of the debt or damages has been repaid before the institution of the`
  line `proceedings, interest shall not be allowed under this section for the period after such repayment.`
  line
  line `(2) Where, in any such proceedings as are mentioned in sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) judgment, order or award is given for a sum which, apart from interest on damages, exceeds`
  line `four thousand rupees, and`
  line
  line `(b) the sum represents or includes damages in respect of personal injuries to the plaintiff or any`
  line `other person, or in respect of a person's death,`
  line
  line `then, the power conferred by that sub-section shall be exercised so as to include in that sum interest on`
  line `those damages or on such part of them as the court considers appropriate for the whole or part of the period from the date mentioned in the notice to the date of institution of the proceedings, unless the court`
  line `is satisfied that there are special reasons why no interest should be given in respect of those damages.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) shall apply in relation to--`
  line
  line `(i) any debt or damages upon which interest is payable as of right, by virtue of any`
  line `agreement; or`
  line
  line `(ii) any debt or damages upon which payment of interest is barred, by virtue of an express`
  line agreement;
  line
  line `(b) shall affect--`
  line
  line `(i) the compensation recoverable for the dishonour of a bill of exchange, promissory note or`
  line `cheque, as defined in the Negotiable Instruments Act, 1881 (26 of 1881); or`
  line
  line `(ii) the provisions of rule 2 of Order II of the First Schedule to the Code of Civil Procedure,`
  line `1908 (5 of 1908);`
  line
  line `(c) shall empower the court to award interest upon interest.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (32363)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Interest payable under certain enactments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00041_197814_1517807325128&sectionId=32363&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00041_197814_1517807325128
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in section`
  line `3, interest shall be payable in all cases in which it is payable by virtue of any enactment or other rule of`
  line `law or usage having the force of law.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding as aforesaid, and without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of subsection (1), the court shall, in each of the following cases, allow interest from the date specified below to`
  line `the date of institution of the proceedings at such rate as the court may consider reasonable, unless the`
  line `court is satisfied that there are special reasons why interest should not be allowed, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) where money or other property has been deposited as security for the performance of an`
  line `obligation imposed by law or contract, from the date of the deposit;`
  line
  line `(b) where the obligation to pay money or restore any property arises by virtue of a fiduciary`
  line `relationship, from the date of the cause of action;`
  line
  line `(c) where money or other property is obtained or retained by fraud, from the date of the cause of`
  line action;
  line
  line `(d) where the claim is for dower or maintenance, from the date of the cause of action.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (32364)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Section 34 of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 to apply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00041_197814_1517807325128&sectionId=32364&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00041_197814_1517807325128
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act shall affect the`
  line `provisions of section 34 of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908).`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (32365)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00041_197814_1517807325128&sectionId=32365&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00041_197814_1517807325128
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) As from the commencement of this Act, the Interest`
  line `Act, 1839 (32 of 1839) and any other law corresponding thereto in force in any State immediately before`
  line `such commencement shall stand repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of this Act shall not apply to any suit or other legal proceeding pending at the`
  line `commencement of this Act and the provisions of the corresponding law applicable immediately before`
  line `such commencement shall, notwithstanding the repeal of such law by sub-section (1), continue to apply to`
  line `such suit or other legal proceeding.`
  line
  line `(3) The mention of particular matters in sub-section (2) shall not be held to prejudice or affect the`
  line `general application of section 6 of the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897), with regard to the effect of`
  line repeal.
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
